<p>I have that homework to write a SQL query that: </p>  <ol> <li>Selects countries where a total number of inhabitants (population) in all the cities is greater than 400 </li> <li>Selects names of countries that have no buildings at all.</li> </ol>  <p>There is a tables definitions</p>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/nasbJ.jpg" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/nasbJ.jpg" alt="http://imgur.com/hLZZ90F"></a></p>  <p>I)</p>  <pre><code>SELECT c1.Name FROM Country c1 JOIN City c2 ON (c1.CountryID = c2.CountryID)  WHERE NOT EXISTS         (SELECT *           FROM City          WHERE Population &lt; 400) ; </code></pre>  <p>Why isn't this correct ? I'm not getting any records.</p>